FBIS4-354 "drafr068_a_94014" FBIS-AFR-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda Kigali Erupts in Violence; Ministers Killed Kigali Erupts in Violence; Ministers Killed Dozens of Aid Workers Killed AU0804105394 Paris AFP in English 1034 GMT 8 Apr 94 AU0804105394 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Brussels, April 8 (AFP) -- Several dozen Rwandan employees of aid organisations in Kigali have been murdered by Rwandan troops, the organisation Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) said here Friday [8 April]. A director of MSF-Belgium, Georges Dallemagne, said in a statement that the aid workers had been killed by members of the Presidential Guard.
